Ad Text:
As the Senior Data Privacy Officer you will play a pivotal role as part of the leadership team within a growing data function, and within a large enterprise-wide organisation. With your expertise across data privacy, you will work within the function to support and enable data programs, some very specific to AI, and work to building up the data privacy framework through to implementation.

Reporting to the Chief Data Officer, you will be working closely with the senior leadership group across data governance, AI, program delivery, and work closely with the legal team, as well as the head of security. This role will also require you to work with executives and the board, across all things data privacy.


This role will work across a range of areas, and will include:   

Embed privacy into major technology initiatives such as cloud, analytics, and artificial intelligence.
Provide clear direction and advice to executives and the Board on privacy matters.
Act as a trusted advisor across the enterprise on all aspects of data protection.
Ensure compliance with privacy laws across Australia, New Zealand, and other jurisdictions.
Lead privacy risk and impact assessments, incident responses, and audits.
Strengthen privacy awareness through training and education across all teams.
Collaborate with Legal, Technology, and operational leaders to embed privacy controls.
Support integration of privacy practices during mergers, acquisitions, and business growth.
Work closely with business leaders to guide privacy practices within strategic plans.
Develop strong relationships with internal teams to drive accountability and compliance.
Build effective partnerships with vendors and suppliers, managing risks and ensuring standards are upheld.
To be considered for this role, you will need to be able to demonstrate your experience:

Working within a complex organisation to embed privacy into major technology initiatives such as cloud, analytics, and artificial intelligence.
Experience in the creation of a data privacy roadmap within a complex organisation operating in multiple regions.
Expert knowledge of privacy laws spanning Australia & New Zealand
Strong capability in managing the data journey end-to-end, from collection through to minimisation and secure disposal.
Proven track record in designing and sustaining privacy frameworks that reflect best practice.
Confident project leader with the ability to engage stakeholders and communicate clearly at all levels.
A background in Legal or Risk is essential for this position
To be considered for this role, you must be an Australian Permanent Resident or Australian Citizen

7+ years of experience in data engineering, data science, or analytics roles.

Experience with Power BI, RPA tools (e.g., Power Automate, Workato Genie, UiPath), and machine learning frameworks.

Excellent problem-solving, communication, and stakeholder engagement skills.

Ad Text:
Job Description

We are looking for a talented and motivated individual to join our Analytics Team, where you'll play a pivotal role in supporting the Workforce and Innovation division within KPMG's Tax practice. This role is ideal for candidates passionate about data, technology, and problem-solving, with a desire to drive innovation and provide cutting-edge solutions in a collaborative environment.

As an integral member of our team, you will focus on designing, developing, and delivering advanced analytical solutions using automation, data-driven insights, and the latest technologies. Your work will align with KPMG's LEAP strategy, a firm-wide approach focused on Leading Edge Automation and Processes to enhance efficiency, improve client outcomes, and drive innovation in the services we provide.

Your Opportunity

Working with the senior engagement team across multiple clients and projects

Designing, building and optimising client analytical solutions

Work closely with the analytics team in building, optimising and productionising new analytical solutions and models

Build, maintain and deploy private libraries for scalable solutioning

Build and maintain PowerBI dashboards

Growing our portfolio of services by developing innovative solutions, tools or dashboards leveraging client data

Involvement in identifying trends and innovation in data platforms to inform the future development of solutions for our clients and evolving our data analytics platform

Actively adding value by bringing innovation and knowledge into designing and operating solutions as well as sharing knowledge across the team

How are you Extraordinary

A commercial and analytical mindset with complex problem-solving skills

Well-developed written and verbal communication skills, including the ability to influence and present your ideas with impact to clients and other key stakeholders

3+ years of data integration and analytical experience within Workforce, HR and Payroll

3+ years of experience with programming python

Hands on experience in building and deploying analytical solutions for large scale data use cases within Databricks

Extensive and proficient skills in Microsoft Azure (Devops CI/CD pipelines, functions, App services, Containers, SQL server, Databricks)

Attention to detail with strong problem-solving skills

Additional Information

Please note that applications will close on the 23rd of October 2025.

KPMG is a professional services firm with global outreach and deep sector experience. We work with clients across an array of industries to solve complex challenges, steer change and enable growth. 

Our people are what make KPMG the thriving workplace that it is and what sets us apart is that we know great minds think differently. Collaborate with a team of passionate, highly skilled professionals who’ve got your back. You’ll build relationships with unique and diverse colleagues who will provide you with the support you need to be your best and produce meaningful and impactful work in an inclusive, equitable culture.

At KPMG, you’ll take control over how you work. We’re embracing a new way of working in many ways, from offering flexible hours and locations to generous paid parental leave and career breaks. Our people enjoy a variety of exciting perks, including retail discounts, health and wellbeing initiatives, learning and growth opportunities, salary packaging options and more.

Diverse candidates have diverse needs. During your recruitment journey, information will be provided about adjustment requests. If you require additional support before submitting your application, please contact the Talent Attraction Support Team.

At KPMG every career is different, and we look forward to seeing how you grow with us.

In the lead-up to the creation of the Australian Retail Council, which is to be formed through the amalgamation of the ARA and NRA, we’re on the search for a Senior Economist for the organisation.

This newly established Senior Economist position will play a strategic and hands-on role in delivering high-impact, original economic analysis to shape and elevate the economic narrative around the retail sector’s contribution to the Australian economy. 

The role will work in partnership with the also newly established Chief Policy Officer & Chief Economist, and alongside members of the policy team, in framing an agenda that responds to the highest order policy and economic priorities for Australia. It will provide analysis around key sectoral issues – including technological disruption, international competition, supply chain resilience and disruption, regulatory burden, workforce pressures, sustainability, retail crime and consumer dynamics – to elevate ARC’s input to national economic and policy debates.  

The role includes carriage for developing compelling economic insights and helping steer a program of evidence-based research. It is anticipated the role will bring to life existing third-party analysis but also develop proprietary tools for better capturing and communicating the value of the sector to a wide range of audiences, including the government, media, members, partners, industry stakeholders and the broader Australian community. 

The position will provide regular presentations and reports to Members on the state of the retail economy. It will also have significant interaction with the CEO, Chief Industry Engagement Officer and Principal Media Advisor. 

About the Role

This role is a significant growth opportunity to elevate your skills, build networks and above all, lift understanding of the retail community.

Key responsibilities will include:

Lead economic analysis and forecasting on retail trade, consumer spending, labour markets, and macroeconomic trends
Assess the economic impacts of regulations, taxation, and policy changes affecting the retail sector
Prepare economic impact assessments and contribute to major policy submissions, including the national wage case and federal budget
Monitor and interpret key economic data from ABS, RBA, Treasury, and other relevant sources
Design, implement, and analyse member surveys to gather industry intelligence
Manage original research projects and data collection initiatives to support advocacy and strategy
Provide economic insights to inform ARC’s strategic planning and policy agenda
Build and maintain strong relationships with government agencies, industry groups, community stakeholders, and ARC members to inform economic analysis and advocacy.
Represent ARC publicly at forums, events, and on social media, while providing tailored economic and policy briefings to members and partners.
Collaborate with Marketing & Partnerships to develop economic reports, data visualisations, and targeted content for key audiences.

About You

Proven experience in economics, preferably with an industry body, think tank, consultancy and/or government
Skilled in stakeholder relationship management, especially in respect of Australia’s pre-eminent economic agencies
Strong analytical and research skills, including proficiency in relevant quantitative software and data tools
Expertise in economic analysis, including familiarity with input-output tables and CGE models
Capacity to synthesize complex information
A strong communicator – able to articulate and present persuasively in internal and external forums, including an ability to convey complex ideas to non-technical audiences
An understanding of the Australian media landscape
Skilled in project management

About Us

The Australian Retail Council will be formed through the amalgamation of the Australian Retailers Association (ARA) and National Retail Association (NRA). It will represent a $430 billion sector that employs 1.4 million Australians, making it the largest private sector employer in the country.

We promote flexible working arrangements for all employees which allows balancing working from home and working from our offices.  

We encourage all applicants, including Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander people, Australian South Sea Islander people, people with disability, LGBTIQ and culturally diverse candidates to apply.

To Apply:

If you are interested in joining a highly respected membership organisation that values respect, integrity, collaboration, accountability, and a focus on excellence, please apply.

Please submit your CV and a Cover Letter addressing the selection criteria.

Applications close 31 October 2025. Only shortlisted candidates will be contacted.

THIS IS A PARENTAL LEAVE CONTRACT

Competitive Salary and annual remuneration reviews.
Health & wellness benefits to support your physical and mental well-being.
Remote work model with co-working options available.
Supportive team – Fun, caring colleagues with regular team-building activities and social events.
Career experiences – Lateral, vertical, and rotational opportunities for development.
Generous leave – Including birthday leave, a Joy day every quarter, and extra time off over Christmas.
A happy, respectful and energetic work environment where 95% of employees recommend working at JobAdder (check out our Glassdoor reviews!)

The Role:

Manage the activities and performance of Business Analysts across multiple product teams, located in Australia and Vietnam.
Provide mentorship, coaching, and development opportunities to BA's at all levels.
Oversee and support Business Analysts who have Quality Assurance responsibilities, ensuring they are effective in both BA and QA functions.
Set standards for BA practices, documentation, tooling, and facilitation techniques.
Collaborate with Product Management, Engineering, and Design leadership to ensure alignment on delivery goals and priorities.
Receive objective-based assignments, and determine resources and support needed to meet schedules and goals.
Ensure Business Analysts are aligned to the highest priority initiatives and contributing effectively across the journey teams.
Contribute directly to one development journey team as a Senior Business Analyst by:
- Leading requirements discovery and documentation
- Facilitating grooming and estimation sessions
- Supporting sprint readiness and prioritisation
- Delivering clear, testable, business-aligned user stories

Expertise: Deep knowledge of Agile development and the SaaS product lifecycle. Experience leading cross-functional teams and managing change is essential.

At TL Consulting, we simplify modern complexity with advanced, sustainable engineering. As a proudly Australian-owned consultancy with over 15 years of experience, we empower businesses to innovate and achieve measurable outcomes through scalable, cloud-native solutions. Our 50+ consultants operate across key sectors including banking, financial services & insurance (BFSI), government, retail, education, and entertainment. This cross-industry expertise allows us to deliver customer-centric solutions that combine deep technical capability with a clear understanding of each client’s strategic vision. Our approach leverages proven, scalable blueprints tailored to your business direction—enabling accelerated outcomes, maximized ROI, and sustainable long-term adoption.

We maintain strategic partnerships with organizations that share our vision for a cloud-native future. Through our collaborations with Microsoft, GitHub, and Databricks, we ensure our capabilities stay aligned with evolving best practices. These partnerships also provide access to innovation programs, co-funding opportunities, and dedicated support—helping us accelerate time-to-value for our clients.

About the role

As the Data Solutions Architect, you will spearhead the development, growth, and strategic direction of the data engineering practice within our consultancy. Your role will focus on leading a team of data professionals, managing client engagements, and ensuring the delivery of high-quality, data-driven solutions that address client challenges. You will work closely with both internal teams and clients to help organizations leverage data for better decision-making, innovation, and growth.




KEY RESPONSIBILITIES

Practice Leadership & Development:

Define the strategic roadmap for the data engineering practice, aligning it with overall company goals.

Identify emerging trends, technologies, and opportunities to continuously evolve the practice.

Lead and orchestrate innovation initiatives aiming to mature the organisation’s data capabilities and solutions.

Develop service offerings that meet client needs, including data strategy, BI, Artificial Intelligence, advanced analytics, and data governance.

Foster a culture of innovation and continuous learning within the team.

Client Engagement & Solution Delivery:

Lead high-impact client engagements, guiding teams in the delivery of end-to-end data analytics solutions.

Provide expertise in the areas of data strategy, business intelligence, predictive analytics, and data management.

Collaborate with clients to understand business objectives and design tailored data-driven solutions.

Ensure projects are delivered on time, within scope, and meet quality standards.

Build and maintain strong, long-term relationships with key clients to ensure repeat business.

Team Leadership & Development:

Manage and mentor a team of data engineers and analysts, promoting collaboration and career growth.

Recruit, retain, and develop talent within the data engineering team.

Conduct regular performance reviews and provide feedback to enhance team capabilities.

Foster a collaborative environment that encourages innovation and best practices.

Business Development & Sales Support:

Support business development efforts by working closely with the sales team to identify and pursue new opportunities.

Lead and contribute to proposal writing, client presentations, and pre-sales activities.

Act as a subject matter expert (SME) during client discussions, showcasing the value of data solutions in tackling business problems.

Identify potential partnerships and collaborations that can enhance the practice’s offerings.

Thought Leadership:

Serve as the face of the data engineering practice in industry forums, conferences, and events.

Publish white papers, blogs, and case studies to showcase the consultancy’s capabilities and success stories.

Stay abreast of industry trends, emerging tools, and methodologies, sharing insights with clients and internal teams.


SKILLS & EXPERIENCE

Required Skills and Qualifications:

Education: Bachelor’s degree in engineering, Computer Science, or a related field. Master’s degree or MBA preferred.

Experience:

10+ years of experience in data analytics, business intelligence, or related data domains.

5+ years of experience in a consulting or professional services environment.

Proven experience in leading data engineering teams and delivering client-focused solutions.

Technical Skills:

Expertise in data analytics tools and platforms (e.g., SQL, Python, R, Apache Spark, Tableau, Power BI).

Expertise in Azure services and analytics platforms such as Databricks, Synapse and MS Fabric.

Knowledge of other cloud platforms (e.g. AWS, Google Cloud) is a plus.

Familiar with DMBOK and/or TOGAF frameworks.

Expertise with data lake modelling such as Kimball (Star Schema) and Data Vault modelling.

Strong understanding of machine learning, predictive analytics, and data visualization techniques.

Soft Skills:

Strong clients focus and ensure effective relationships are in place with key client stakeholders to deliver that service.

Excellent client relationship management skills with the ability to explain complex technical concepts to non-technical stakeholders.

Strong stakeholder management skills interfacing with diverse stakeholders. i.e., General Manager, Head of Architecture, Solution Architecture.

Solid experience in relationship management, conflict resolution, influencing and negotiation.

Must be able to work independently but also lead Consulting engagements in a highly matrixed environment (especially for short-term engagements).

A team player who can liaise effectively with a diverse group of delivery teams to ensure a positive experience for the customer.

Ability to manage multiple projects simultaneously and prioritize effectively in a dynamic environment.

Excellent verbal and written communication skills.

Preferred Qualifications:

Consulting experience in various industries (e.g., finance, healthcare, manufacturing).

Azure and Databricks certifications are a plus.

Experience with Agile methodologies and project management tools.


WHY JOIN US

Be part of a dynamic consultancy firm that values innovation, growth, and professional development.

Lead a growing practice at the forefront of data-driven business transformation.

Work with diverse, top-tier clients across multiple industries, delivering impactful solutions.

Competitive salary and benefits package.

Career development and growth opportunities within a rapidly expanding organization.




This is a Sydney based, permanent opportunity and will be hybrid in nature. No agencies please. Candidates must have valid visa with full work rights in Australia. Visas will not be transferred or sponsored.

Job Title: Platform Manager - Data & AI - Transformation - Hawthorn East
Ad Text:
We’ve been trusted to serve Aussie communities since 1914 and grown to become a top 30-listed on the ASX with over 115,000 team members and a portfolio of iconic brands. At Coles Group, you’ll not only get to make a difference to millions of Aussie lives—you’ll also get to see your impact.

About the team

As the way we shop continues to evolve, our Data and Artificial Intelligence Team keeps us at the cutting edge. Driven by our innovative, inclusive, and forward-thinking culture, we’re constantly looking at ways to reinvent the shopping experience for our customers and build the next generation of digital retailing. 

The Data and Artificial Intelligence within the broader Coles Technology Team focuses on building data collection and analytics capabilities to uncover customer, product, and operational insights. Providing data driven support to our users and enabling Coles to be a data driven organisation.

About the role

For this exciting position within our Data and Artificial Intelligence team, we are seeking an experienced Platform Manager – Transformation to lead end-to-end planning, execution, and delivery of platform transformation programs ensuring alignment to enterprise Data & AI strategy and business outcomes.

Working closely with the Senior Platform Manager – Transformation, your main responsibilities will include the following but not be limited to the below: 

Drive the adoption of modern cloud infrastructure, containerisation, microservices, Infrastructure as Code and automation frameworks.
Collaborate closely with architecture, security, data governance, and compliance teams to embed standards and controls into the evolving platform.
Manage risks, dependencies, and resources proactively to maintain project momentum and delivery quality.
Facilitate knowledge sharing and cross-team collaboration to accelerate transformation and build organisational capability.
Deliver timely reporting and transparent communication on project status, risks, and opportunities to senior leadership.
Identify opportunities to optimise costs, improve performance, and enhance scalability within the platform environment.
Foster a culture of experimentation, innovation, and accountability within the transformation team.

We are looking for a versatile leader to lead, mentor, and grow a team of platform engineers, fostering a culture of innovation, collaboration, and high performance.

You will inspire and motivate cross-functional teams to embrace change and deliver transformational outcomes aligned with enterprise goals whilst acting as a change agent, promoting Agile methodologies, DevOps practices, and continuous delivery culture throughout transformation initiatives.

Experience required
Proven years of experience in platform management, IT transformation, or technical program management in data and AI environments.
Proven track record delivering complex platform transformation or cloud migration projects.
Working experience with cloud platforms (Azure, Snowflake, Databricks), containerisation (Docker, Kubernetes), and automation tools (Terraform, Ansible).
Familiarity with modern data platform technologies, AI/ML infrastructure, and scalable architecture patterns.
Experience in agile methodologies and cross-functional team leadership.
Understanding of data governance, security, and compliance requirements in large enterprises.

Commercial Skills and Formal Qualifications
Strong project and program management skills with ability to drive delivery in complex environments.
Technical expertise in cloud infrastructure, platform automation, and modernisation frameworks.
Excellent communication and stakeholder management abilities.
Leadership skills with experience managing technical teams.
Relevant certifications in cloud platforms, project management, or transformation methodologies are advantageous.
Bachelor’s Degree in Computer Science, Engineering, or related field.

What’s in it for you?
Flexible working options: We know that work is only one part of your life, so we actively encourage a positive work-life balance and provide hybrid working options to help you achieve it.
Office perks: Take advantage of our gym facility and fitness classes, free parking, BBQ area, mini-Coles supermarket, fooderie hub where you can sample new products before they hit the shelves, school holiday program and so much more when you come in.
Discounts: Eligible team members receive 5% discount all year round on your Supermarket and Liquor online and in-store purchases. We also offer additional periods of double discount (10%) at various times throughout the year. As well as hotdeals exclusive to team members that translate into additional savings.
Reward through recognition: Give and receive recognition, linked to our Coles values, through our digital recognition platform ‘mythanks’. You can accumulate points to redeem in the online shop for exciting gifts and electronic gift cards from an extensive range of retailers.
Opportunities for learning and development: No matter where you start within our diverse business, you’ll have experiences, exposure, and education to satisfy you. Discover and explore a variety of career development programs and job-specific training.
Paid parental leave: We understand how important your life outside work is and offer permanent team members paid parental leave to support you in balancing work and family.
Investment in your future: Our annual team member share plan offer allows eligible team members to make regular pre-tax salary sacrifice deductions to purchase Coles Group shares.

About the recruitment process

We’re continuing to build a gender equitable team, and a culture that is just as diverse, inclusive and welcoming as the communities we serve. We are committed to creating a workplace that is safe and respectful for our team. We encourage applications from people of all ages, cultures (including Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples), abilities, sexual orientation and gender identities.

We’re happy to adjust our recruitment process to support candidates with disability. For further information and additional contact details visit the ‘Our Recruitment Process’ section of our careers site or email inclusionrecruitment@coles.com.au

The role 
As a Senior Data Engineer, you’ll lead the design and technical delivery of data projects, leveraging Microsoft Azure Data Services. 

You’ll work closely with our Data Warehouse, Analytics, and Platform teams, as well as the Project Management Office, to ensure successful end-to-end delivery.

What you will be doing:

This role serves as the lead for data projects, responsible for designing and delivering solutions that meet both new and existing client requirements.
You’ll lead and contribute to projects across a diverse client base, ranging from mid-market to enterprise environments.
Working closely with the Data Architect and key stakeholders, you’ll translate complex data needs into effective, scalable solutions.
You’ll partner with teams across Data & AI, Brennan Digital, and the Project Management Office to ensure seamless and successful client delivery.
What skills and experience you bring:

Strong experience across data engineering with extensive project experience.
Deep and hands-on experience designing, planning and maintaining scalable data infrastructure and data products in complex environments.
